                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18020714-9-victim158 t18020714-9-viclabel48"></join> at Lambeth, he has a shop, <placeName id="t18020714-9-crimeloc49">No. 57, Broad-street, Bloomsbury</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18020714-9-crimeloc49" type="placeName" value="No. 57, Broad-street, Bloomsbury"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18020714-9-crimeloc49" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18020714-9-off46 t18020714-9-crimeloc49"></join>; On the 5th of June, I was at the George and Crown, having a pint of beer after my dinner, about half-past two o'clock, nearly opposite my master's; I observed the prisoner reaching over some Chinese railing that was fixed in the front of the shop; I saw him try the hatch door to get in; I then saw him put his foot upon the scraper, and get over the rails, and in at the shop window; I ran over from the public-house, and when I came there, he had got this piece of floor-cloth under his arm, he had not got out of the shop; I stopped him, and took it from him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I was in a very bad way, and could not do any work; I don't know any thing about the oil-cloth. <rs id="t18020714-9-verdict50" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18020714-9-verdict50" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 65.</p>
